# GitHub Collaborators (Code Owners)

## Overview
This file specifies code owners for different parts of the ISO-TP-C project. GitHub uses this file to determine who should review pull requests.

## Syntax
```
path/to/file_or_directory @username1 @username2
# or
path/to/file_or_directory @org/team
```

## Code Owners Configuration

### Root and Configuration Files
All configuration and build files should be reviewed by maintainers:
```
# Build configuration
/CMakeLists.txt @maintainer
Makefile @maintainer
/.github/ @maintainer
/vars.mk @maintainer

# Documentation
/README.md @maintainer
/LICENSE @maintainer
```

### Source Code
Core ISO-TP implementation requires careful review:
```
# Core library source
/Src/ @maintainer
/Inc/ @maintainer
```

### Tests
Test code should be reviewed for coverage and correctness:
```
# Unit and integration tests
/tests/ @maintainer

# Test configuration
*.test.yml @maintainer
```

### Documentation
Documentation changes should maintain consistency:
```
# API documentation
/docs/ @maintainer

# Code review guidelines
.copilot-instructions.md @maintainer
.github/BRANCH_PROTECTION_SETUP.md @maintainer
.github/pull_request_template.md @maintainer
```

---

**Note:** Replace `@maintainer` with your actual GitHub username or organization team.

Example with actual usernames:
```
/Src/ @john-dev
/Inc/ @john-dev
/tests/ @test-team
/docs/ @documentation-team
/.github/ @john-dev
```

---

